:** Explore → Specify → Test → Implement → Verify → Document\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++### Phase 0: Explore\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Read all files in the affected area of the codebase.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Identify existing patterns, naming conventions, and architectural decisions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Review related tests to understand expected behavior.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Update progress.md with exploration findings.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++### Phase 1: Specify\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Write a specification to `specs/{{ task_id | lower }}-spec.md`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Include: problem statement, technical approach, edge cases, acceptance criteria.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Each acceptance criterion must have a VERIFY command.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++### Phase 2: Test Development\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Write tests BEFORE implementation, derived from the specification.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Tests must FAIL before implementation (Red phase).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- After this phase, test files are LOCKED — do not modify assertions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++### Phase 3: Implement\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Implement the minimum code needed to pass all tests.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- One sub-task at a time, commit each logical unit.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Type hints on all function signatures.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Follow existing patterns.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++### Phase 4: Verify & Document\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Run full test suite and quality checks.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Update CHANGELOG.md, progress.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- No questions — document assumptions in ESCALATIONS.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Do not modify locked test assertions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Log new dependencies to ESCALATIONS.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Commit per sub-task: `feat(scope): summary [{{ task_id }}]`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Common Pitfalls (from recurring verify feedback)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++These are the top reasons tasks get PASS WITH NOTES instead of clean PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Avoid them on the first attempt:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- **Always include a migration** when adding or modifying database columns.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  A new model or column without a migration is a deployment gap.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- **Commit all changes** before the verify phase begins. Uncommitted work\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  is flagged as blocking by the verifier.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- **Stay in scope** — only commit work under this task's ID. Do not bundle\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  changes from adjacent subtasks or refactor unrelated code.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- **Add indexes on new FK columns** in `__table_args__` when adding\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  foreign key relationships.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- **Keep CHANGELOG entries consistent** with actual behavior. Do not copy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  descriptions from other tasks or specs without verifying they match\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  the implemented code.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Validation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Run before final commit:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++All must pass.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Use the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+diff --git a/sdp/templates/candidates/verify/v001.md b/sdp/templates/candidates/verify/v001.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+new file mode 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+index 0000000..8b15903\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+--- /dev/null\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++++ b/sdp/templates/candidates/verify/v001.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+@@ -0,0 +1,97 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++# Verification: Task {{ task_id }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Task:** {{ task_description }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Tier:** {{ tier }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++You are the VERIFY agent for this task. The LEAD agent has completed their work.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{% if acceptance_criteria %}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Acceptance Criteria\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{{ acceptance_criteria }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{% endif %}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Review Checklist\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++1. **Review recent commits:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   ```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   git log --oneline -5\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   git diff HEAD~3 --stat\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++2. **Review code changes:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   ```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   git diff HEAD~3\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{% if tier != \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" %}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++3. **Review specification** (if T2/T3):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   Read `specs/{{ task_id | lower }}-spec.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{% endif %}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++4. **Check ESCALATIONS.md** for any flagged issues.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++5. **Run the test suite:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   ```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Evaluation Criteria\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Evaluate the work against these five dimensions:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++1. **Correctness**: Does the output match the requirements/spec?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++2. **Completeness**: Are there gaps, missing edge cases, or unhandled scenarios?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++3. **Consistency**: Does the output follow established patterns and conventions?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++4. **Security**: Are there vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++5. **Quality**: Does the output meet the quality gates for this phase?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Write your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++`sdp/verification/{{ task_id | lower }}-verify.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Do not use a different filename or directory.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Use this format:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++```markdown\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++# Verification Report — {{ task_id }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Date:** [today]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Artifacts Reviewed:** [list files reviewed]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Correctness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++[assessment]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++[assessment]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++[assessment]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++[assessment]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++[assessment]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- [ ] [Issue — severity: blocking/minor]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Verdict: [PASS | PASS WITH NOTES | FAIL]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++[specific items to address]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Commit the verification report.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Use the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+diff --git a/sdp/templates/claude/lead_t1.md b/sdp/templates/claude/lead_t1.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+new file mode 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+index 0000000..5835695\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+--- /dev/null\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++++ b/sdp/templates/claude/lead_t1.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+@@ -0,0 +1,44 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++<!--\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  sdp-cli agent-specific template for claude\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  Edit this file to tune how claude handles lead_t1.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  The shipped default lives at src/sdp/prompts/templates/lead_t1.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  Delete this file to revert to the default.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++-->\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++# Task {{ task_id }}: {{ task_description }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{% if acceptance_criteria %}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Acceptance Criteria\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{{ acceptance_criteria }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{% endif %}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Tier:** {{ tier }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Instructions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Handle this directly. Skip broad discovery and do not write a spec.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++1. Read only the file(s) you expect to change and the closest relevant tests.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++2. Make the smallest change that satisfies the task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++3. Add or update a regression test when behavior changes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++4. Run focused validation, then broader checks if needed.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++5. Commit as soon as the change works: `<type>(scope): summary [{{ task_id }}]`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Stay in scope; no unrelated cleanup.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Follow existing patterns and type hints.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Record blocking assumptions in `ESCALATIONS.md`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Do not finish with uncommitted changes you introduced for this task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Do not clean, revert, commit, or otherwise normalize unrelated pre-existing\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  workspace changes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Validation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Run before committing:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++pip install -e '.[dev]'\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++pytest tests/ -x --tb=short\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++ruff check src/ tests/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++mypy src/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+diff --git a/sdp/templates/claude/lead_t2.md b/sdp/templates/claude/lead_t2.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+new file mode 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+index 0000000..a6fd0bd\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+--- /dev/null\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++++ b/sdp/templates/claude/lead_t2.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+@@ -0,0 +1,51 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++<!--\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  sdp-cli agent-specific template for claude\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  Edit this file to tune how claude handles lead_t2.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  The shipped default lives at src/sdp/prompts/templates/lead_t2.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  Delete this file to revert to the default.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++-->\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++# Task {{ task_id }}: {{ task_description }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{% if acceptance_criteria %}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Acceptance Criteria\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{{ acceptance_criteria }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{% endif %}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Tier:** {{ tier }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Instructions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Work directly. Do not write a specification file or a phase summary.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++1. Read the likely entrypoint files and nearby tests, not the whole repo.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++2. Implement the smallest viable solution first.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++3. Add or update tests around the changed behavior.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++4. Run focused checks while iterating, then the full validation below.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++5. Commit each logical unit once it passes. Do not wait until the very end.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Defaults\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- If the task is clear, code first and add tests immediately after.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Prefer explicit file paths and existing patterns over open-ended exploration.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Fix the task; do not refactor adjacent code unless required.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Record assumptions or follow-up risks in `ESCALATIONS.md` instead of blocking.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Stay in scope and keep changes minimal.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Follow project conventions from `AGENTS.md`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Do not stop with uncommitted tracked changes you introduced for this task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Do not clean, revert, commit, or otherwise normalize unrelated pre-existing\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  workspace changes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Use commit format: `<type>(scope): summary [{{ task_id }}]`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Validation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Run before final commit:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++pip install -e '.[dev]'\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++pytest tests/ -x --tb=short\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++ruff check src/ tests/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++mypy src/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+diff --git a/sdp/templates/claude/verify.md b/sdp/templates/claude/verify.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+new file mode 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+index 0000000..a6aade4\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+--- /dev/null\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++++ b/sdp/templates/claude/verify.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+@@ -0,0 +1,76 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++<!--\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  sdp-cli agent-specific template for claude\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  Edit this file to tune how claude handles verify.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  The shipped default lives at src/sdp/prompts/templates/verify.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  Delete this file to revert to the default.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++-->\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++# Verification: Task {{ task_id }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Task:** {{ task_description }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Tier:** {{ tier }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Verify by executing the change and checking outcomes. Do not write a deep design review.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{% if acceptance_criteria %}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Acceptance Criteria\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{{ acceptance_criteria }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{% endif %}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Review Checklist\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++1. Check `git status --short`, but make the dirty-worktree decision task-scoped.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   Uncommitted changes introduced by the lead for this task are blocking.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   Pre-existing unrelated dirty or untracked files are notes only; do not ask the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++   lead to clean, revert, or commit unrelated workspace state.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++2. Review the task commit(s) and changed files only.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++3. Run the smallest relevant test command first. If scope is broad or unclear, run the full validation below.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++4. Compare observed behavior against the acceptance criteria and changed code paths.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++5. Report only reproducible issues, missing behavior, regressions, or real risks.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Blocking vs Notes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- `FAIL`: failing checks, missing required behavior, regressions, or uncommitted task-scoped tracked work.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- `PASS WITH NOTES`: behavior is correct but minor cleanup or follow-up remains.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- `PASS WITH NOTES`: also use this when acceptance passes but the repository has\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++  unrelated pre-existing dirty state outside the task scope.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- `PASS`: acceptance criteria are met and no blocking issues remain.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Write your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++`sdp/verification/{{ task_id | lower }}-verify.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Do not use a different filename or directory.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++If you need a full validation pass, run:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++pip install -e '.[dev]'\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++pytest tests/ -x --tb=short\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++ruff check src/ tests/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++mypy src/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++Use this format:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++```markdown\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++# Verification Report - {{ task_id }}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Date:** [today]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Artifacts Reviewed:** [files and commits]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Commands Run:** [commands]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Acceptance Criteria Check\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++[met / not met, with evidence]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- [ ] [blocking/minor] [issue]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- [ ] None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Verdict: PASS | PASS WITH NOTES | FAIL\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\