\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++The verification added `preview_score`, `critique_score`, and `revise_score` with matching tests and default thresholds, and those tests are passing. However, the acceptance-level runtime behavior is incomplete: the self-critique revision pipeline is not invoked from the music composition/playback path, so new pieces are still generated and played from direct `score_from_mood()` calls.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++The new APIs and unit tests cover the AC-1..AC-7 conditions at an isolated module level, including revision bounds and identity checks. But the feature is not end-to-end integrated into the runtime, and no targeted integration test proves pre-playback critique happens in actual piece construction.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++There are no style or interface violations in the new module, and the changes are internally coherent with existing `Score`/`generative_scores` structures. Runtime callsites remain untouched and continue using older generation flow, so composition consistency is unchanged rather than improved for this task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++No new credentials, network calls, filesystem writes, or insecure parsing paths were introduced in the new code. Test harness modifications are read-only and do not add new exposures.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- `pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x` passed (2168 passed, 0 failed).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Existing suite health is good, but functional requirement coverage is shallow for real playback/runtime wiring.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Several hardening concerns from prior escalations (bootstrap identity startup flow) are already addressed in the existing branch (`bootstrap_identity()` + `FirstBootAnnouncer` observed in existing daemon paths and `tests/test_first_boot.py`), unchanged by this task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- [x] **Issue — severity: blocking**: New self-critique logic is not wired into the active composition pipeline. `my-claw/tools/senseweave/tracker_compiler.py` and `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py` continue to call `score_from_mood(...)` directly in piece generation; `revise_score(...)` from `senseweave.self_critique` is never imported or used by composition/playback flow.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Verdict: FAIL\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Integrate the new `revise_score(...)` path into score generation before tracker/build or playback handoff (both gate-backed and fallback paths).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Add an integration test that verifies a piece goes through critique/revision before being finalized for playback, with assertions that failed metrics can trigger one bounded rewrite attempt and that the final score is selected from the two-pass result.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+diff --git a/tests/test_archive_paths.py b/tests/test_archive_paths.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+new file mode 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+index 0000000..98a157c\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+--- /dev/null\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++++ b/tests/test_archive_paths.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+@@ -0,0 +1,101 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Tests for heavy archive/storage path selection