CHANGELOG.md:5:- Added the CypherClaw narrative memory search HTTP slice (T-001@20260502T001347Z): new `cypherclaw.narrative_api` exposes `POST /memory/search` through a FastAPI `create_app(...)` factory, wraps deploy-side `NarrativeMemory` via lazy import, supports injected memory searchers for tests, normalizes common result shapes into ranked `{id, text, similarity, domain, metadata}` responses, and defensively honors `domain_filter` for shared/Deniable/CypherClaw memory separation. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` pins ranking, domain filtering, single-domain requests, validation, and downstream failure handling.
CHANGELOG.md:30:- Added the missing CCS-028 sample-usage journal seam for tracker pieces: `senseweave.usage_journal` now serializes the richer per-piece sampler fields (`started_at`, `mode`, `samples_used`, `transformations`, `clicks`) while preserving the legacy `timestamp` / `samples_played` aliases, `music_tracker_runtime.ScheduledTrackerEvent` now carries sample-gesture metadata through playback emission, `duet_composer.py` now records actual emitted sample-lane events into the post-piece journal hook, and new regression coverage in `tests/test_usage_journal.py`, `tests/test_music_tracker_runtime.py`, and `tests/test_usage_journal_integration.py` composes a short score-tree piece end to end and proves the written journal entry contains populated sample usage, transformations, and arc payoff data.
CHANGELOG.md:74:- Added arrangement automation curves to tracker playback: `music_tracker.py` now derives `arrangement_curve` from section rhythm, writes row-point automation for `density`, `master_amp`, and `reverb_send`, shapes note velocity across each lane's active window, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` / `duet_composer.py` now expose and apply interpolated automation to the live master bus during the section. Low density also thins optional color/counter runtime events while preserving melody and bass continuity.
CHANGELOG.md:85:- Tightened the user-boot camera ownership path too: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now deduplicates the local observer/presence daemons and starts `room_presence_daemon.py` in shared-observer mode, which prevents repeated boot invocations from piling up dozens of competing camera loops on the live box.
